Suggested file roles
infra/k8s/rules/myapp/Chart.yaml: declares the Helm chart.

infra/k8s/rules/myapp/templates/prometheus-rules.yaml: contains the templated PrometheusRule.

infra/k8s/rules/myapp/dev/values.yaml: dev thresholds.

infra/k8s/rules/myapp/staging/values.yaml: staging thresholds.

infra/k8s/rules/myapp/prod/values.yaml: prod thresholds.

infra/k8s/rules/myapp/base/prometheus-rules-base.yaml: optional non-templated reference or fallback, if you want to keep a plain manifest too.


infra/
  k8s/
    rules/
      myapp-alerts/
        Chart.yaml
        .helmignore
        values.yaml           # base (prod-ish) defaults
        values-dev.yaml
        values-staging.yaml
        values-prod.yaml
        templates/
          prometheus-rules.yaml

You will then:
    - Use Helm to render the PrometheusRule into plain YAML per env.

    - Pipe the rendered YAML to kubectl apply